                <![CDATA[
                        <img src="https://tinkermeer.github.io/sungjilee.github.io/media/posts/29/DSC00756.JPG" alt="" />
                    Reminiscing about the past brings a mixture of happiness and sadness. There is comfort in the memories, yet also sorrow in knowing those&hellip;
                ]]>
            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <p><img src="https://tinkermeer.github.io/sungjilee.github.io/media/posts/29/DSC00756.JPG" class="type:primaryImage" alt="" /></p>
                
  <p>
    Reminiscing about the past brings a mixture of happiness and sadness. There is comfort in the memories, yet also sorrow in knowing those moments are gone forever. Distance from my loved ones gave rise to a profound longing for connection. Over time, however, I came to realize that my existence no longer moved continuously within the rhythm of their lives. Years of separation formed an invisible yet unbearable barrier between us.<br>Driven by this bittersweet awareness, I seek to reclaim fleeting moments from the past. Using needle and thread, I stitch into faded photographs to bridge the void between memory and the present. The act of sewing becomes both restoration and meditation—a way of retrieving memories and transforming them into a renewed visual language.
  </p>

