                    <p><img src="https://tinkermeer.github.io/sungjilee.github.io/media/posts/28/Lee_my-neighbor-Aaronda.jpg" class="type:primaryImage" alt="" /></p>
                
  <p>
    This piece reflects on the memory of my former neighbor and the quiet intimacy we once shared. Ordinary moments—chatting, smiling, tending gardens together—may seem insignificant, yet they often become essential fragments of our lives.<br>Through the process of weaving and stitching, I revisit these memories and reconstruct the emotional connections shaped by time and distance. The act of making becomes a way of preserving relationships that continue to enrich my life even after they have faded into the past.
  </p>

