  <p>
    This work captures moments of video conversations with my father, whom I am unable to meet in person. Feelings of longing and emotional absence lead me to stitch into an old, empty cellphone case.<br>Through weaving and stitching, I attempt to bridge the distance between past and present. The repetitive act of sewing becomes a way of revisiting memories while confronting his physical absence. The cellphone case, once an object of communication, is transformed into a space where memory, loss, and connection coexist.
